    27‚Üí# nested documents cause pure Python to raise RecursionError (which is OK),
    28‚Üí# but mypyc binary wheels will crash unrecoverably (not OK). According to
    29‚Üí# mypyc docs this will be fixed in the future:
    30‚Üí# https://mypyc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/differences_from_python.html#stack-overflows
    31‚Üí# Before mypyc's fix is in, recursion needs to be limited by this library.
    32‚Üí# Choosing `sys.getrecursionlimit()` as maximum inline table/array nesting
    33‚Üí# level, as it allows more nesting than pure Python, but still seems a far
    34‚Üí# lower number than where mypyc binaries crash.
